This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring January 2012 as National Mentoring Month. The proclamation highlights the importance of mentors in helping young Americans overcome challenges and prepare for their future. Mentors are praised for their positive influence and their ability to inspire confidence and success in children. The government is working to expand mentorship opportunities, including partnering with businesses, funding mentorship programs for children from military families, and engaging faith and community groups. The article encourages adults to become mentors and make an investment in the future of the nation. The proclamation calls upon public officials, business and community leaders, educators, and Americans to observe National Mentoring Month with appropriate activities and programs.